OL,3,CElle Edwards murder: Gunman loses
OL,4,Cappeal against prison sentence
OL,6,FMark Rhind KC, representing Chapman,
OL,7,Ftold the court his sentence was
OL,8,F"manifestly excessive".
OL,10,FThe barrister said the challenge was
OL,11,Fnot seeking to "minimise the
OL,12,Fculpability of Mr Chapman or the
OL,13,Fseriousness of what he's done".
OL,15,FHe said it was conceded it was an
OL,16,F"extremely serious case" with
OL,17,F"numerous aggravating features",
OL,18,Fadding that, whatever the outcome of
OL,19,Fthe appeal bid, Chapman would spend
OL,20,F"decades in prison, perhaps his entire
OL,21,Flife in prison".
