OL,3,CElle Edwards murder: Gunman loses
OL,4,Cappeal against prison sentence
OL,6,FBut Nigel Power KC, representing the
OL,7,FCrown Prosecution Service, said the
OL,8,FCourt of Appeal "should be slow to
OL,9,Finterfere with the assessment of the
OL,10,Ftrial judge who heard all of the
OL,11,Fevidence in this case".
OL,13,FRejecting Mr Rhind's arguments, he
OL,14,Fsaid: "What we have is a man living a
OL,15,Fcriminal lifestyle involved or
OL,16,Fassociated with revenge attacks who
OL,17,Fimmediately upon hearing of the
OL,18,Flocation of people he was
OL,19,Fdetermined... to take out of the game,
OL,20,Fwas able to act."
